// escurel — Tailscale ACL FRAGMENT (forward-looking).
//
// This is a fragment of the substrate's tailnet policy file, NOT a
// standalone ACL. The operator folds these entries into the substrate
// repo's Tailscale policy (an `infra/modules/tailscale/` PR per
// substrate-platform skill ref 06). Inventing a tag here does nothing
// until that PR lands and the module mints auth keys carrying the tag.
//
// IMPORTANT — current substrate reality (skill ref 06): app workloads
// do NOT yet have per-app tailnet identities. escurel allocations run
// on cli nodes carrying `tag:cli`; "tailnet-only" today means "no
// urlprefix- Fabio tag, reachable via Consul DNS over the node-level
// tailnet." The `tag:dz-escurel` rows below are FORWARD-LOOKING: they
// describe the intended per-app isolation once the per-app-tag module
// ships. Until then, the effective policy is the substrate default
// (`tag:ops -> tag:cli`, inter-node traffic on the private network).
//
// Tag name reconciliation: substrate.md §7 prose uses `tag:escurel`;
// the substrate.md § Naming-convention table (the authoritative,
// post-PR-#61 source) uses `tag:dz-escurel`. This fragment uses
// `tag:dz-escurel` to match the shared substrate naming convention.
//
// Access pattern (substrate.md §7):
//   - tag:dz-escurel reaches tag:srv ONLY for the Vault template
//     (secret fetch at task start). It does NOT initiate to
//     tag:agents — escurel is not behind Triton.
//   - tag:ops (operators + CI ops identity) may reach escurel's
//     Prometheus /metrics :9090 over the tailnet. Admin tooling and
//     the export shipper reach the admin surface via the authenticated
//     HTTP MCP service (port 8080, behind Fabio/OIDC), not a
//     tailnet-only port.
//   - tag:agents (the agent pool) does NOT reach escurel directly;
//     only Triton (on tag:cli) does, and that is over Fabio /
//     Consul-routed HTTP, not a tailnet ACL grant.
{
  "tagOwners": {
    // Operator-only: a substrate PR allocates the auth-key binding.
    "tag:dz-escurel": ["autogroup:admin"]
  },

  "acls": [
    // Operators + CI ops identity reach escurel's tailnet-only
    // surface: Prometheus /metrics :9090.
    {
      "action": "accept",
      "src": ["tag:ops"],
      "dst": ["tag:dz-escurel:9090"]
    },

    // escurel reaches the Vault/Consul/Nomad servers ONLY for the
    // Vault secret template + Consul service registration. Vault is
    // :8200; Consul DNS/HTTP :8500/:8600 are node-level and already
    // covered by the substrate default, listed here for intent.
    {
      "action": "accept",
      "src": ["tag:dz-escurel"],
      "dst": ["tag:srv:8200"]
    }

    // NO rule granting tag:dz-escurel -> tag:agents. escurel is a
    // knowledge-base data store, not a Triton upstream; it must not
    // initiate to the agent pool (substrate.md §7).
  ],

  // Operator note: public MCP/WS/REST ingress is NOT a tailnet ACL
  // concern — it flows internet -> Hetzner LB :443 -> Fabio (on cli)
  // -> Consul-routed -> escurel alloc (skill ref 03 + substrate.md §8).
  // The tailnet ACL governs only the tailnet-only surface (metrics)
  // and the Vault secret fetch.
  "ssh": []
}
